{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"blank-clout-greed","description":"## What\n\nAdd **lease-based self-healing** on top of the ref-lock primitive so a crashed pass-holder never\nwedges the reconciler beyond one lease interval. Builds directly on the C1 primitive.\n\n- **Relative-duration lease** (clock-skew-proof, the DynamoDB-lock-client pattern): expiry is\n  judged from the holder's own heartbeat progression / HLC, not by comparing two clones' wall\n  clocks.\n- **Heartbeat renewal at ~lease/3:** a `renew()` on `_ref_lock` that CAS-updates the blob's\n  `hlc_heartbeat` (and bumps `fence`) while the holder still owns the ref.\n- **CAS-break-on-expiry:** a contender may steal the lock **only** when the current lease is\n  expired, by CAS-replacing the blob against the exact old oid it observed. Because the steal is a\n  compare-and-swap against the observed oid, a **double-break race resolves to exactly one\n  winner** — the loser's CAS fails and it retries/backs off.\n- Live in `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_ref_lock.py` (extends C1); still no reconciler\n  orchestration wiring (that is C3).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `_ref_lock.py` supports `renew()` (heartbeat CAS-updates `hlc_heartbeat`/`fence` for the\n      owner) and lease-expiry evaluation using a relative duration, not absolute wall-clock diff.\n- [ ] A contender can CAS-break only an **expired** lease; breaking a live lease is refused.\n- [ ] Regression test: two contenders racing to steal one expired lock — exactly one wins, the\n      other observes CAS failure and does not also acquire (single-winner invariant).\n- [ ] Regression test: a holder that keeps heartbeating at ~lease/3 is never stolen from.\n- [ ] Non-integration suite green.","id":"7522-129b-1380-418c","parent_id":"6c9c-811f-6dc4-40e7","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Lease + heartbeat + CAS-break-on-stale self-healing (single-winner)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783216079196182001,"uuid":"e68aee92-a517-4478-8d99-b67ec3c89187"}